==English==
===Etymology===
From ''Toxophilus'', the title of a 1535 book by [[w:Ascham|Ascham]] intended to mean ‘lover of the bow’, from Greek [[τοξον]] ‘bow’ + [[φιλος]].

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /tɒk'sɒfɪlʌɪt/

===Adjective===
{{en-ad|toxophilite}}
# pertaining to [[archery]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun|toxophilite|toxophilites}}
# an [[archer]]